In this letter, President Barack Obama informs the Chairmen and Ranking Members of the House and Senate Committees on Appropriations, the Chairman and Ranking Member of the House Committee on Foreign Affairs, and the Chairman and Ranking Member of the Senate Committee on Foreign Relations that he has determined and reported to Congress that the suspension of the right to bring an action under title III of the Cuban Liberty and Democratic Solidarity (LIBERTAD) Act of 1996 is necessary for 6 months beyond February 1, 2011. He states that this suspension is in the national interests of the United States and will help expedite a transition to democracy in Cuba. The letter is signed by President Barack Obama.